The paper proposes a general-purpose approach to discovering active learning strategies using reinforcement learning. The paper is focused on machine learning and optimization, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Markov decision processes, which is a common technique in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV) as domains where the proposed approach can be applied. Finally, the paper discusses the use of state and action spaces, which is a common concept in the field of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
